        <div>
            <p>The ministerial redbox has been the primary destination for state papers since they came into government in the mid-19th century. Redbox Copilot was initially envisioned as a way to leverage AI to search through thousands of documents, interrogate them and summarise them into tailored briefings.</p>
            <p class="mt-4">Following an Evidence House hackathon in 2023 which focussed on creating AI solutions to make civil service more efficient, we spun up a small prototyping team with members from the No 10 Innovation Fellowship and Evidence House. Within two months the prototype was being actively trialled within three different Private Offices with Cabinet Office. The trial gave us many future avenues of development and also helped test our rigorous AI safety mechanisms. With this alpha trial complete, we’re now broadening the scope of Redbox Copilot to address the entire civil service.</p>
            <p class="mt-4">Just like ministers, civil servants deal with a wealth of information on a day to day basis. We’re now in the process of building the next generation of Redbox Copilot, which will become a powerful efficiency "multitool" for all departments; built by government, for government.</p>
        </div>
